title: Swain Invitational Overruns Enger Park Again
text:
Swain Invitational Overruns Enger Park Again 
By Norman Seawright III October 3, 2015 Updated Oct 3, 2015 at 10:46 PM CDT 
Duluth, MN (NNCNOW.com) -- Cross country runners overran Enger Park Golf Course for the annual Swain Invitational, featuring more than 2,000 runners from 29 schools in Minnesota and Wisconsin. 
The varsity race was a 5000m run around the course. 
Click here to subscribe to our daily newsletter. 
Varsity Girls A:Watertown-Mayer's Hannah Truniger took first (18:50.4), followed by Carlton's Erika Fox. Perham won as a team, and Ely took eighth. 
Varsity Girls AA:Forest Lake's Emma Benner won (18:03.6), and Cloquet's Anja Maijala finished fourth. As a team, Forest Lake won, and Duluth East was second. 
Varsity Boys A:Spooner's Dan Pederson won (16:08.8)Mora won the team competition, and Northwestern took fourth. 
Varsity Boys AA:Totino-Grace's Kevin Dado won (16:19.8), and Isaac Boedigheimer (Cloquet) finished fourth. Mounds View won team competition, and Cloquet took third.
